	(10,'1','2',2,'alma astral','soul star','img/contents/5ea1cadcda89098465935dedb068ab0a.jpg','<p>With Traffic&#39;s comprehensive SEO services in the world, you can radically improve your search rankings on all the biggest search engines including Google, Yahoo, and Bing. We make sure that your business is always in search engines&#39; top results whenever a relevant query is made via any of the leading search engines.</p>\n\n<p>Our optimisation strategy is based on robust market analysis that our SEO experts conduct at the very start of the project. All the SEO techniques we apply are fully compliant with the industry standards. These are just some of the things that set Traffic apart from other run-of-the-mill SEO companies in the worldSEO strategy To impress Google&rsquo;s SERP, you need a strategy - full of diverse techniques and high quality practices. Only a good strategy can see your SEO through. At Traffic, we specialize in helping businesses mastermind and implement digital marketing strategies. Using a blend of conventional and advanced SEO techniques, we ensure your website ranks high for terms relevant for your specific business.</p>\n',NULL,'<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">SEO strategy </span></h3>\n\n<p>To impress Google&rsquo;s SERP, you need a strategy - full of diverse techniques and high quality practices. Only a good strategy can see your SEO through.</p>\n\n<p>At Traffic, we specialize in helping businesses mastermind and implement digital marketing strategies. Using a blend of conventional and advanced SEO techniques, we ensure your website ranks high for terms relevant for your specific business</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">SEO keyword </span></h3>\n\n<p>Research Keyword research is an integral element of SEO. It is a delicate science involving research into search patterns, keyword relevancy, market analysis, and even consumer behavior. Do things right and you&rsquo;ll have a firm foundation for your entire SEO campaign; do things wrong and your SEO campaign will become a money pit.</p>\n\n<p>At Traffic, we specialize in smart keyword research. We offer advice on all aspects of your SEO strategy, and help you conduct detailed, insightful keyword research to get everything started the &#39;right&#39; way. Being a local SEO company, we understand regional search patters, and how these variances can boost up your site&rsquo;s SEO.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Competitor analysis </span></h3>\n\n<p>Clever SEO involves digging into your competition&rsquo;s back link profile, conducting content audits, domain analysis to see what they are doing. Using this information to make your digital marketing even smarter is an essential ingredient of cost effective SEO.</p>\n\n<p>Traffic, being a clever SEO agency, enables you keep an eye on your biggest competitors, and helps you beat them. We understand that it isn&rsquo;t always the flashiest websites that&rsquo;s doing the most active trade &ndash; treats emerge from the unlikeliest of sources. Our SEO helps you counter these hidden threats.</p>\n\n<p><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">On site SEO </span></p>\n\n<p>Selecting the right keywords and competition analysis is half the battle, turning this information into a workable &ldquo;on site/on page&rdquo; SEO plan is the key to success.</p>\n\n<p>Traffic&rsquo;s SEO not only helps you to improve your website, but also enables you to match keywords with target pages. By assisting you to enhance site accessibility, loading time, and architectural structure, we assist you to create a killer SEO campaign. Find out more about our design expertise.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Off site SEO </span></h3>\n\n<p>Once the site is ready, SEOs start building links to open the site up for traffic. Linking building is not exactly a science, it is an art, which takes years to master. Simply building irrelevant links, can actually lead your site into trouble.</p>\n\n<p>From writing quality guest posts, to placing links on credible site, and social sharing &ndash; we know many offsite SEO tricks.</p>\n',NULL,'izodiac','0','2014-09-05 09:09:17',NULL),
	(12,'1','2',2,'carta astral',NULL,'img/contents/18e0652bf58416c24d33f50de0cfb89d.jpg','<p>Email marketing is by far the most frequently used (and misused) digital communications channel by organisations in the Middle East. Over 80% of brands and companies surveyed stated that Email was their primary method of keeping thier audiences up to date with their services and products.</p>\n',NULL,'<p>New, trackable communication methods have kickstarted the region&rsquo;s transition to an online world, with computer, tablet and smart phone developments making this a seamless process for the great majority of us. 31% of Middle East internet users now subscribe to email newsletters relating to companies and brands, while 20% have made purchases as a direct result of an email newsletter.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Integral</span>&nbsp;</h3>\n\n<p>For many businesses, email marketing is an integral tool in their digital marketing strategy. An ease of access to return on investment (ROI) figures partnered with the generation of a wealth of metrics makes for one of the most successful channels in the digital marketer&rsquo;s current arsenal. With 84% of GCC based companies stating an increase in their digital marketing budgets by up to 50% within the coming year, it is only set to become an even more influential means of communication.</p>\n\n<p>However, many organisations fail to optimise their email marketing strategies often resulting in email campaigns that do more harm than good.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Data Base&nbsp;</span></h3>\n\n<p>We are often asked &ldquo;So how much do you charge for an email list&rdquo; and our answer is always the same. We don&rsquo;t charge anything because we don&rsquo;t sell or rent email lists, we help you to develop your own targeted and relevant database. By doing so, we help to ensure that the people who receive emails from you want to do so and are interested in you, your products or your services, increasing open and click through rates.</p>\n\n<p>With an abundance of unsolicited, unappealing and annoying emails currently flooding the inboxes of internet users, it doesn&rsquo;t take much to turn potential customers into brand saboteurs, making it that much harder to develop meaningful relationships with these potential customers.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Our email marketing suite</span></h3>\n\n<p>Our system allows you to generate and send out high quality HTML emails based on pre designed templates within minutes and with absolutely no technical knowledge. We help segment your database into groups based on your individual needs. For example, if you have an offer which is relevant to male members of the Saudi market, aged 24-35 who have purchased products from you within the last 6 months, we can ensure your promotion reaches exactly this audience.</p>\n\n<p>If you are interested in sending out quality HTML emails that are tested to display succesfully across 99% of all email clients such as Gmail, Outlook and Thunderbird, please get in touch with us today for a demonstration.</p>\n',NULL,'izodiac','0','2014-09-05 10:09:00',NULL),
	(13,'1','2',2,'prosperidad',NULL,'img/contents/92f25c75f02c1396c50d4d89a1c42f42.png','<p>What is an app? The term &ldquo;app&rdquo; is short for &ldquo;application&rdquo;. Within digital marketing, when we refer to an app, we are generally talking about a mobile application such as those that you, and millions of others, use every day on smart phones around the world, or a campaign application on your corporate Facebook page. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>When strategically developed and targeted, custom Facebook applications can support your outbound and inbound marketing or business goals with trackable results. With a Facebook population of over 22 million across the Middle East there&rsquo;s no question that your audience is ready.</p>\n',NULL,'<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Custom applications</span></h3>\n\n<p>By rolling out unique and engaging promotions across your social media channels, you give your company or brand the ability to engage with your target market in a real and meaningful manner, increasing reach of information and customer conversion.</p>\n\n<p>A key benefit of custom applications, is the ability to gather user data as part of the process. &nbsp;This data can then be used to stay in touch with your audience, to drive key business decisions and to help direct your marketing strategies.</p>\n\n<p>How many people within your customer base are between the ages of 25 and 34? How many of these customers are male or female? How many live in Bahrain, Saudi Arabia or the greater GCC area? Any number of questions can be posed and answered giving you incredible insight into your target market.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Keep it simple</span></h3>\n\n<p>We have rolled out a whole raft of custom applications for our customers, ranging from simple sign ups with custom landing pages, ensuring that your visitors are prompted to become a part of your community before being able to participate, through to fully customised treasure hunts, leading users to engage with each and every online and offline marketing channel available. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>We have learnt that the key to a successful campaign is ensuring that, no matter how many channels you wish to activate, the barriers to entry are as few as possible and that requirements necessary to engage are as simple as possible.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:#6A8F30\">Return of investment</span></h3>\n\n<p>Of course, a core concept of digital and social media marketing is the ability to track and analyse your return on investment. We ensure that, for every custom campaign developed, we track all the key analytical touch points you would expect: How many people visited the page? How many users clicked on the links? How many users shared content? How many users converted into fans? etc.</p>\n\n<p>By comparing this information against details gathered either before or after the campaign, we are able to assign a baseline to your standard traffic and conversion, therefore assigning any gains to activities undertaken in association with your campaign. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>For a clear example of an effective custom Facebook application, check out our case study on the &lsquo;Be A Part of Our History&rsquo; 2013 Porsche Boxster campaign.</p>\n',NULL,'izodiac','0','2014-09-05 10:09:48',NULL),
	(11,'1','2',2,'revolucion lunar',NULL,'img/contents/ddf03cf9f95b2f1c8913fdedd9997227.jpg','<p>The use of social media throughout the Middle East has exploded in recent years, with a diverse demographic of users embracing mainstream channels such as Facebook, Twitter, YouTube, LinkedIn and more. Thanks to the unstoppable driving force that is the internet, combined with rapid technological advancements, social media has become a main feature of daily life. It has been used in a wide variety of functions in the Arab world, from social and political causes to communications and marketing. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Whether brands approve of it or not, many of these consumers are discussing their products and services through online channels. As the maturity and understanding of social media has developed in regional internet users, so has the opportunity to create measurable return on investment by incorporating these channels within existing marketing strategies.</p>\n',NULL,'<h3><span style=\"color:rgb(106, 143, 48)\">Social domination</span></h3>\n\n<p>The Middle East&rsquo;s internet usage is dominated by social networking and email, with some 88% of users actively engaging in social networking on a daily basis. With 34% making purchases through online channels, it&rsquo;s clear that the buying process for many consumers is heavily influenced by what is being said on social networking channels. This is made even clearer when you consider that 73% of internet users in the GCC state that their decision to buy products and services has been influenced by online reviews and discussions.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:rgb(106, 143, 48)\">The stats have it&nbsp;</span></h3>\n\n<p>Platforms such as Facebook, Twitter and YouTube are teeming with social activity from regional users and contain established communities that represent many organisations&rsquo; target audiences. Throughout the GCC alone the Facebook penetration rate has been measured at 98% of internet users, while Twitter has a penetration of 36%. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>61% of internet users in the GCC actively discuss brands, products and services through online mediums, whether on social networks, forums or blogs. Their opinions can be shared with hundred or even thousands of other internet browsers &ndash; essentially the internet has allowed anyone with an opinion to be heard by a very large audience if they choose to make their opinions public.</p>\n\n<h3><span style=\"color:rgb(106, 143, 48)\">Maintenance &amp; Opmisation</span></h3>\n\n<p>Our approach to social media marketing aims to develop authentic, two-way communications. We have learnt that creating relevant online communities consisting of engaged stakeholders and consumers is what leads to revenue generation. Combining individual research with our experience and expertise, we take a holistic approach that combines strategic goal setting, public relations and community management, making sure our clients receive the full benefit of having a great social media presence. &nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Clients such as Audi, Spring of Culture and Porsche have benefited from our services &ndash; view case studies here.</p>\n',NULL,'izodiac','0','2014-09-05 10:09:29',NULL),
